{"article_id":"BEhoVHrrBlG97wnO","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Months of conflict and confusion over a fraud-tainted House race in North Carolina ended Thursday","depth":9},{"id":1,"text":"with the State Board of Elections ordering a new election .","depth":9},{"id":2,"text":"The five-member board ' s unanimous vote for a redo capped a monthslong investigation and four days of dramatic testimony before the board about an absentee ballot scheme","depth":9},{"id":3,"text":"linked to the campaign of Republican Mark Harris .","depth":9},{"id":4,"text":"The Nov. 6 results","depth":11},{"id":5,"text":"that showed Mr. Harris leading Democrat Dan McCready by 905 votes","depth":11},{"id":6,"text":"have been in limbo","depth":10},{"id":7,"text":"because of fraud allegations ,","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"leaving the 9th Congressional District seat empty in the new Congress .","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"The board was tasked with reviewing the evidence","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"and deciding whether to certify the Nov. 6 results","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"or order a new election in the district ,","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"which spans the area between Charlotte and Fayetteville .","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"Shortly before the vote , Chairman Bob Cordle said","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"the \" illegal activity \"","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"that the board uncovered","depth":10},{"id":16,"text":"undoubtedly","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"had \" tainted the results of the entire election . \"","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"\" I believe","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"the people of North Carolina deserve a fair election","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"and deserve to have their votes counted properly , \"","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"he said .","depth":7},{"id":22,"text":"It ' s rare for a state to call a new election","depth":6},{"id":23,"text":"to resolve a disputed House race .","depth":6},{"id":24,"text":"The last time was in the 1974 election for Louisiana ' s 6th Congressional District ,","depth":6},{"id":25,"text":"when a malfunctioning voting machine caused a disputed outcome","depth":7},{"id":26,"text":"and a state court ordered a new election .","depth":7},{"id":27,"text":"Mr. Harris fought tooth and nail","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"to have his Nov. 6 win certified ,","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"including mounting a court challenge ,","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"but he abruptly reversed course at Thursday ' s hearing .","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"\" Through the testimony","depth":12},{"id":32,"text":"I have listened to over the past three days ,","depth":12},{"id":33,"text":"I believe","depth":12},{"id":34,"text":"a new election should be called .","depth":12},{"id":35,"text":"It has become clear to me","depth":11},{"id":36,"text":"that the public ' s confidence in the 9th District seat general election has been undermined to an extent","depth":12},{"id":37,"text":"that a new election is warranted , \"","depth":12},{"id":38,"text":"he said .","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"The reversal followed inconsistencies in Mr. Harris ' testimony and revelations","depth":8},{"id":40,"text":"that his campaign attorney withheld documents relevant to the investigation .","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"After spending three hours on the stand Thursday ,","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"Mr. Harris returned from an extended lunch break","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"and said","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"he had a change of heart .","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"He also announced","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"that he was hospitalized last month with a severe infection","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"and suffered two strokes .","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"\" Though I thought","depth":11},{"id":49,"text":"I was ready to undergo the rigors of this hearing","depth":12},{"id":50,"text":"and am getting stronger ,","depth":12},{"id":51,"text":"I clearly am not ,","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"and I struggled this morning with both recall and confusion , \"","depth":11},{"id":53,"text":"he said .","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"Mr. Harris maintained","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"that neither he nor leaders of his campaign knew about the scheme","depth":12},{"id":56,"text":"to \" harvest \" absentee ballots","depth":13},{"id":57,"text":"- illegal in North Carolina -","depth":13},{"id":58,"text":"that allegedly was orchestrated by political operative Leslie McCrae Dowless .","depth":11},{"id":59,"text":"Red Dome Group , a consulting firm","depth":12},{"id":60,"text":"hired by the Harris campaign ,","depth":12},{"id":61,"text":"contracted Mr. Dowless","depth":12},{"id":62,"text":"to run the absentee ballots operation .","depth":12},{"id":63,"text":"Mr. Dowless refused to testify at the hearings .","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"His attorney , Cynthia Adams Singletary , told reporters","depth":8},{"id":65,"text":"that he denies wrongdoing .","depth":8},{"id":66,"text":"North Carolina Republican Party Chairman Robin Hayes said","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"he respected Mr. Harris ' decision .","depth":8},{"id":68,"text":"\" This has been a tremendously difficult situation for all involved ,","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"and we wish him the best","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"as he recovers from his illness and subsequent complications , \"","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"he said .","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"\" We will continue to work with legislators and investigators on how we can improve the electoral system","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"so that these kinds of situations can be avoided in the future . \"","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"North Carolina Democratic Party Chairman Wayne Goodwin said","depth":7},{"id":75,"text":"the wrongdoing was traced to Mr. Harris and the Republican Party .","depth":7},{"id":76,"text":"\" North Carolina Republicans ,","depth":11},{"id":77,"text":"following Mark Harris ' lead ,","depth":11},{"id":78,"text":"repeatedly lied to the people of the 9th District ,","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"silenced their voices","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"and undermined our entire state ' s faith in our democracy .","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"This saga could only have ended in a new election ,","depth":9},{"id":82,"text":"and we look forward to repairing the harm","depth":11},{"id":83,"text":"dealt by Republicans","depth":11},{"id":84,"text":"and giving the people of the 9th District the representative","depth":11},{"id":85,"text":"they deserve , \"","depth":11},{"id":86,"text":"he said .","depth":7},{"id":87,"text":"Kristen Clarke , president and executive director of the Lawyers ' Committee for Civil Rights Under Law , cheered the decision for the new election .","depth":6},{"id":88,"text":"\" It ' s no surprise","depth":8},{"id":89,"text":"that Mark Harris is throwing in the towel","depth":9},{"id":90,"text":"and calling for a new election for North Carolina ' s 9th Congressional District .","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"Over the past four days , the evidence of rampant absentee ballot fraud continued to mount","depth":10},{"id":92,"text":"and made clear","depth":11},{"id":93,"text":"that the outcome of this election was completely illegitimate , \"","depth":11},{"id":94,"text":"she said .","depth":9},{"id":95,"text":"\" The lesson","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"that all Americans should take from this","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"is that ballot fraud and voter suppression remain rampant in our country","depth":10},{"id":98,"text":"and stand as grave threats to our democracy . \"","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"The board will set the date of the election at a future meeting .","depth":3},{"id":100,"text":"Earlier , Mr. Harris testified","depth":7},{"id":101,"text":"that Mr. Dowless had assured him","depth":8},{"id":102,"text":"they were not breaking the law .","depth":8},{"id":103,"text":"\" He said","depth":8},{"id":104,"text":"we don ' t touch ballots","depth":9},{"id":105,"text":"or take ballots , \"","depth":9},{"id":106,"text":"he said .","depth":7},{"id":107,"text":"Documents and testimony","depth":10},{"id":108,"text":"presented by election officials","depth":10},{"id":109,"text":"indicated otherwise .","depth":9},{"id":110,"text":"They included cases","depth":9},{"id":111,"text":"of collecting absentee ballots","depth":10},{"id":112,"text":"and filling in ballots for some voters .","depth":10},{"id":113,"text":"It is illegal in North Carolina for anyone other than a voter or a close relative to mail in an absentee ballot ,","depth":9},{"id":114,"text":"but that ' s what they did ,","depth":9},{"id":115,"text":"according to testimony by workers","depth":9},{"id":116,"text":"involved in the scheme .","depth":9},{"id":117,"text":"Election Director Kim Strach has called it \" a coordinated , unlawful and substantially resourced absentee ballot scheme . \"","depth":6},{"id":118,"text":"As he planned his 2018 run ,","depth":8},{"id":119,"text":"Mr. Harris said","depth":8},{"id":120,"text":"he was introduced to Mr. Dowless as a \" good ol ' boy \"","depth":8},{"id":121,"text":"who \" eats , lived , slept and drank politics . \"","depth":8},{"id":122,"text":"Mr. Dowless had a reputation","depth":8},{"id":123,"text":"for running an aggressive and proven operation","depth":9},{"id":124,"text":"to boost turnout and absentee ballot voting .","depth":9},{"id":125,"text":"Andy Yates , co-founder and senior partner at Red Dome Group , testified","depth":8},{"id":126,"text":"that he did not know what Mr. Dowless was doing .","depth":8},{"id":127,"text":"Mr. Harris ' son John Harris , an assistant U.S. attorney in North Carolina , testified Wednesday","depth":7},{"id":128,"text":"that he warned his father","depth":8},{"id":129,"text":"that the absentee ballot drive looked fishy .","depth":8},{"id":130,"text":"The son ' s testimony also contradicted Mr. Harris ' repeated claim","depth":8},{"id":131,"text":"that no one ever raised red flags about what Mr. Dowless was doing .","depth":8},{"id":132,"text":"\" I had no reason","depth":9},{"id":133,"text":"to believe","depth":11},{"id":134,"text":"that my father or mother knew","depth":12},{"id":135,"text":"Dowless was doing the things","depth":13},{"id":136,"text":"that have been described , \"","depth":13},{"id":137,"text":"the son said .","depth":10},{"id":138,"text":"\" I think","depth":9},{"id":139,"text":"they were lied to ,","depth":10},{"id":140,"text":"and they believed the person","depth":11},{"id":141,"text":"who lied to them . \"","depth":11},{"id":142,"text":"On the stand Thursday , the elder Mr. Harris said","depth":3},{"id":143,"text":"he considered discussions with his 27-year-old son to be \" family conversations \" and not warnings .","depth":3},{"id":144,"text":"He added","depth":3},{"id":145,"text":"that he was \" very proud \" of his son for his legal career and his performance on the stand .","depth":3}],"relations":[{"parent":291,"left":287,"right":290,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":287,"left":244,"right":286,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":244,"left":172,"right":243,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":172,"left":167,"right":171,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":167,"left":158,"right":166,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":158,"left":154,"right":157,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":154,"left":149,"right":153,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":149,"left":147,"right":148,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":147,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":148,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":153,"left":152,"right":8,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":152,"left":151,"right":7,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":151,"left":150,"right":6,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":150,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":157,"left":9,"right":156,"relation":"joint","nuclea